description: To the north, a large mound rises out of the swamp, crowned with short grasses and trees.  Here, the water is very still and stagnant, stinging the nostrils of travelers.  Black birds flit occasionally through the trees, swooping down to the surface of the swamp to catch unwary insects.

To the north, a large mound rises out of the swamp, crowned with short grasses and trees.  Here, the water is very still and stagnant, stinging the nostrils of travelers.  Mosquitoes and fireflies flit occasionally through the trees.
title: [Vornavis, The Bog]
